news.title: Goa HC asks why no action has been taken over 42 notices about land illegalities
news.para: “The panchayat must explain why these notices have not been disposed of till date and also indicate the timeline within which such notices will be disposed of,” the high court stated.

news.title: Water shortage hits builders, construction industry in Coimbatore
news.para: Construction industry players said they were forced to extend the deadline of many projects in the absence of sufficient water to carry out work.

news.title: Kolkata: No mutation certificates to be issued to flat owners if building found illegal
news.para: ​In short, the owner of a flat in an illegal building would be denied ownership status, said a civic official, adding the assessment department would merely make the owner the “person liable to pay tax”.

news.title: HDIL promoters walk out of jail after four years
news.para: On April 5, Bombay HC had granted them bail in two separate cases linked to the alleged Rs 4,000 crore Punjab and Maharashtra Co-operative Bank fraud cases probed by Economic Offences Wing and the subsequent money-laundering case registered by ED in 2019.

news.title: Mumbai: Over 100 teams to be deployed for Dharavi redevelopment survey
news.para: Currently, over 15 teams are doing the survey at Railway land’s Kamala Raman Nagar, 28 of 46 acres of which was transferred by Railway Land Development Authority (RLDA) between Mahim and Matunga to the DRP on March 12.

news.title: NCLAT upholds insolvency proceedings against Tulip Hotels over default of guarantees
news.para: ​On May 16, 2023, the Mumbai bench of National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) had directed initiation of a Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP) against Tulip Hotels over a plea filed by Yes Bank, claiming a default of Rs 900 crore for two corporate guarantees issued by it.

news.title: S&P slashes property giant China Vanke's credit rating to junk
news.para: S&P slashed the rating of China's second biggest developer by sales by a hefty three notches to BB+ from BBB+, leaving it one rung into 'junk' territory, or 'non-investment grade' as it is also known.

news.title: USA: Blue Owl to buy Prima Capital Advisors for $170 million
news.para: Investment firms have been rushing to grab a bigger slice of the commercial real estate market as traditional lenders, which are subjected to harsh regulations, back out on fears of rising defaults due to low occupancy and high interest rates.

news.title: Germany's Galeria sold to US investor Baker and Beetz consortium
news.para: Galeria, the nation's most prominent retailer, earlier this year began the search for new owners after filing for insolvency following the collapse of its parent Signa.

news.title: Real estate drags China’s stocks down
news.para: Ratings agency Fitch revised its outlook on China to negative on Tuesday, citing increasing risks to the country's public finance outlook.

news.title: About 50 societies in Ahmedabad opt for redevelopment in eight months
news.para: Ahmedabad's urban landscape undergoes transformation with a surge in housing redevelopment projects. Navrangpura, Naranpura, and Paldi show potential. High rental demand. Redevelopment favored over moving to the outskirts for comprehensive facilities.

news.title: Sobha reports 28% increase in pre-sales in FY24
news.para: In terms of volume, the sales bookings grew by 8 per cent to 6.08 million (60.8 lakh) square feet from 5.65 million (56.5 lakh) square feet in the previous year.

news.title: ED attaches 1,807 acre land parcel in Sindhudurg in PMC bank scam case
news.para: The Directorate of Enforcement (ED) has attached 413 agricultural land parcels measuring approximately 1,807 acres in Maharashtra's Sindhudurg in connection with a bank loan fraud case of Punjab and Maharashtra Co-operative Bank (PMC).

news.title: Stamp duty collection rise by 60% in Gujarat in FY24
news.para: Gujarat govt's income from stamp duty and registration fee rose by 60% to Rs 13,731.63 crore in 2023-24 due to jantri hike. Property documents registered increased by 35% to 18.26 lakh, with stamp duty revenue at Rs 4,447.87 crore.

news.title: Pune civic body adds over 53,000 new properties in tax ambit in FY24
news.para: As per the civic officials, the properties under PMC’s jurisdiction were around 8 lakh in 2017. Since then, 4.5 lakh properties have been added as 34 areas were merged into the PMC’s limits.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body to resume work on slum rehabilitation project in Mahisakhal
news.para: The housing project, which began in 2013 under the erstwhile Rajiv Awas Yojana (RAY), involves the construction of a G+4 storied building designed to provide better housing for slum dwellers.

news.title: Patna high court directs ED to file action report against erring builder
news.para: The petitioners' counsel, Punit Kumar, alleged that the accused construction company has duped the 42 persons of about Rs 100 crore by not handing them over their apartments in Sai enclave, despite taking hefty amounts in advance.

news.title: Telangana HC issues notice to government over land transfer to Vasavi Real Estate group
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice Alok Aradhe and Justice J Anil Kumar, while agreeing to take up the PIL filed by social worker Chekka Ashok Kumar, sought replies from Rangareddy collector.
